		<item>
		<title>Redis Stubbing with Specmatic Contract Testing</title>
		<link>/updates/redis-stubbing-with-specmatic-contract-testing/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Joel Rosario]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 11 Jul 2023 03:17:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Feature Spotlight]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Updates]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Redis]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Stubbing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">/?p=1625</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Instead of using an actual instance of Redis, we'll stub it out and have the contract test set expectations so that the Redis stub knows what data to return for any query sent to it by the application. Now, when we run the contract tests and the service object does a look up in Redis, it's actually hitting the Redis stub.]]></description>
		
		
		
